                            <comment id="15197258" author="ctang.ma" created="Wed, 16 Mar 2016 12:47:20 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Patch has been uploaded to &lt;a href=&quot;https://reviews.apache.org/r/44910/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://reviews.apache.org/r/44910/&lt;/a&gt; for review.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15197308" author="aihuaxu" created="Wed, 16 Mar 2016 13:27:51 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Yeah. The patch looks good. Only minor issues. +1.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We may remove the function &lt;tt&gt;public static Schema getSchemaFor(InputStream stream)&lt;/tt&gt; completely to avoid leaking if it&apos;s only used by &lt;tt&gt;getSchemaFor(Url)&lt;/tt&gt;. But I know it&apos;s public interface that someone may use it. Just a thought.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15197695" author="ctang.ma" created="Wed, 16 Mar 2016 17:09:42 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=aihuaxu&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;aihuaxu&quot;&gt;aihuaxu&lt;/a&gt; for review. Yeah, I did not remove the API (public static Schema getSchemaFor(InputStream stream)) exactly for the reason as you said. The user should close the passed-in inputstream in his own application.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
